I am getting this insane log spam from some mod in my install able to push my log to new height of 200+Mb. I am hoping someone else has experienced this so that I can save time not hunting the bug down. Yes I know about binary sorting. It doesn't work that great when mods have interdependence and you leave some out splitting the install in half. Just here hoping to save time. The spam only happens upon getting out of the atmosphere,but doesn't stop when re entering. Here is an excerpt. Thanks More info provided at request!

I have no idea how you think anything between that thread and my problem are related...

Anyway still getting this and it is killing my game. Every single craft in orbit upon reaching a periapsis above the atmosphere causes this massive spam of 3 numbers in parentheses. I swear whoever the modder is that put some unlabeled crap to be spammed with the frequency that this is is a terrible terrible person :C. I am in total disbelief that this is only happening to me. I just don't know what to do I did a binary sort of mods on a sandbox save testing that I would get the errors only with a single half of the mods. So tested that half narrowing it down by using a test rocket of stock parts. Had it narrowed down to 5 mods added them back to reconfirm the error and it stopped and didn't come back. I go back to full install and spam return despite adding the half the didn't have the spam. If anyone has actual insight please help! Thanks!
